const title = "Midjourney vs Stable Diffusion: Which AI Art Wins 2026?";
const description = "Midjourney v7 vs Stable Diffusion 3 compared on image quality, control, pricing, and ease of use. Find the best AI image generator for your workflow.";
const faqItems = [
  {
    q: "Is Midjourney v7 better than Stable Diffusion 3?",
    a: "It depends on your priorities. Midjourney v7 delivers superior out-of-the-box image quality with cinematic, artistic results that need almost no tuning. Stable Diffusion 3 offers unmatched control through LoRA models, ControlNet, and IP-Adapter, but requires more technical skill. Choose Midjourney for speed and aesthetics, Stable Diffusion for precision and custom workflows."
  },
  {
    q: "Which is more affordable, Midjourney or Stable Diffusion?",
    a: "Stable Diffusion 3 is free and open source, so you can run it locally at no cost beyond electricity. Midjourney v7 starts at $10 per month for the Basic plan and rises to $30 for the Standard plan. Cloud APIs for Stable Diffusion, such as DreamStudio, charge roughly $0.002 per image, so high-volume commercial users often save money with Stable Diffusion."
  },
  {
    q: "Can Stable Diffusion run on my computer without paying?",
    a: "Yes. Stable Diffusion is free and open source. You need a compatible GPU, ideally an NVIDIA RTX 2060 or better with at least 8GB of VRAM, plus tooling such as Automatic1111 WebUI or ComfyUI. With that setup you can generate unlimited images locally at no cost, though training custom LoRA models still requires significant compute time."
  },
  {
    q: "Which AI image generator gives more control over the output?",
    a: "Stable Diffusion offers far more control. LoRA models allow subject-specific training, ControlNet guides pose and composition through edge detection and depth maps, and IP-Adapter enables style transfer from reference images. Midjourney's control is limited to prompt parameters, aspect ratio, and a few style tags, with no custom model training available."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Midjourney or Stable Diffusion better for beginners?",
    a: "Midjourney is significantly easier for beginners. You describe your vision in natural language and receive beautiful images without any technical setup, model selection, or GPU hardware. Stable Diffusion requires understanding model selection, prompt engineering, negative prompts, and often local GPU installation, which can be overwhelming for first-time users."
  },
  {
    q: "Which tool is better for commercial projects?",
    a: "Both support commercial use. Midjourney's paid plans include commercial usage rights, which simplifies licensing for agencies and brands. Stable Diffusion's open-source license also permits commercial use, but specific community models on platforms like CivitAI may carry their own restrictions, so you must verify each model's license before using it commercially."
  },
  {
    q: "Do Midjourney and Stable Diffusion support inpainting and image-to-image?",
    a: "Yes, both support inpainting and image-to-image workflows. Midjourney offers variation, pan, zoom, and region edit features inside its web interface. Stable Diffusion provides deeper control through ControlNet, img2img, and inpainting tabs in Automatic1111 and ComfyUI, allowing precise mask editing and parameter tuning for every step."
  },
  {
    q: "Which AI image generator is faster?",
    a: "Midjourney generates a batch of four images in roughly 60 seconds on its cloud servers. Stable Diffusion on a modern GPU like an NVIDIA RTX 3060 or better produces a single image in 5 to 15 seconds locally, though complex workflows with LoRA and ControlNet take 15 to 30 seconds. For rapid iteration without hardware investment, Midjourney is more convenient; for raw speed and unlimited volume, local Stable Diffusion wins."
  }
];
